    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look to capitalize on favorable matchups today, with **Jackson Merrill** (65.98) and **Jacob Wilson** (64.91) emerging as our most efficient offensive pillars. **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a strong platoon advantage against the right-handed Castillo, while **Jacob Wilson** is elevated by a park factor boost and a favorable matchup against the 4.43 xERA of Leiter. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.81) remains a locked-in high-floor play despite a neutral platoon, as his sustained xwOBA profile of .384 continues to anchor the heart of our order. Meanwhile, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (60.68) remains a strong start in the two-hole, buoyed by a significant +14% dynamic platoon adjustment against Ashcraft.\n\nOur most difficult decision came at the margins, where **Nolan Schanuel** (47.95) narrowly missed the final cut. While his underlying metrics against Fried are respectable, the optimizer favored the higher volatility and specific order-placement upside of **Miguel Vargas** and **Josh Jung**. We are also closely monitoring **Gunnar Henderson**, whose raw projection was dampened significantly by a -15% dynamic platoon penalty against the left-handed Messick; at a 48.62 score, he remains in the lineup purely for his elite ceiling, though he is currently performing below his typical output against southpaws.\n\nRisk management remains a priority given the scarcity of our stolen base targets. While **Nasim Nunez** and **Brady House** possess the speed profile we crave, both were benched due to poor lineup positioning\u2014notably **Nasim Nunez** dropping to the nine-hole\u2014and tough efficiency projections against the current pitching slate. We are keeping a close watch on the weather and the final lineup cards for any late-breaking shifts that might force us to pivot off these efficiency projections, particularly with **Gunnar Henderson** facing a stiff challenge from Messick.",
